nas-web (2.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of nas-web (renamed from nodeproxy)
  * Built-in health endpoints: /apis/healths, /apis/heartbeat, /apis/ping
  * Admin panel at /np_admin with Basic Auth protection
  * HTTP/2 support via nghttp2
  * Lua 5.4 scripting middleware
  * LRU response cache with RFC 7234 compliance
  * Token bucket rate limiter per IP
  * WebSocket proxying support
  * Static file serving with gzip, ETag, Range support
  * SPA fallback routing
  * Graceful shutdown via SIGTERM/SIGINT (uv_walk)
  * Hot config reload via SIGHUP
  * X-Request-ID tracing header
  * systemd service with auto-restart

